short_description: INC7327134 : P2 : SAP PH1 - Sterling Integrator SHPORD messages to DHL and GEODIS at <10610 - Warwick - United Kingdom>
u_root_cause:
Why 1: Why was the Sterling Integrator (SI) unable to transfer the files from SAP PH1 to External Vendor (Geodis & DHL).
           A1: This was due to the SI perimeter server being inactive and unresponsive to the Sterling Integrator.
           Why 2: Why were SI perimeter servers inactive and unresponsive to the SI?
                  A2: It seemed that the SI perimeter server was not functioning properly in the backend, despite the logs appearing
                         normal upon review.
                        Why 3: Why were the SI parameter servers not functioning properly in the backend?
                               A3: To identify the cause, an IBM PMR was raised, and the IBM team made changes to the hostname of the
                                      external IF for the remote parameter. Additionally, the SI perimeter server application was restarted to
                                      resolve the issue.
Final Root Cause: 
There appeared to be an intermittent issue with the SI perimeter server, where certain configurations were stuck. Refreshing the properties ultimately resolved the issue.

short_description: P2-INC7348276-EMEA-Fuel Injection Systems-Users are facing the issue with  SAP T Code in SAP PN1 System at site 10304 - Iasi - Romania on 03rd Feb'25.
u_root_cause:
Users encountered an issue with the SAP T code in the SAP PN1 system, preventing business users from completing the backflush process using transaction code ZCOGIA.
The issue occurred due to the controlling period not being opened in T- code OKP1, which is required to be maintained by the business at the end of each month This was missed for the period 02/2025.

short_description: Major Incident-P2-INC7387944-Global-Aftermarket-Users are facing slowness issue while accessing SAP PH1 on 28th Feb'25
u_root_cause:
Why 1: Why were the Users not able to access the SAP PH1 Application?
   A1:  The Users weren't able to access the SAP PH1 Application because the SAP Hana Database got rebooted.
      Why 2: Why did the SAP HANA Database get Rebooted?
       A2: The SAP HANA Database got rebooted because of the Microsoft Azure Planned Network Activity.
   Final Root Cause: The physical host node where the VM is running had a networking stack update due to which the VMs got Rebooted and this resulted in a brief loss of connectivity.

P2 - There is a DHCP issue in VLAN 354 with the 10.239.5.0/24 network. Currently, none of our devices are receiving IP addresses, and we cannot access servers
u_root_cause:
- Initially issue was reported for VLAN 354 & VLAN 3
- Due to limited access, From Network End we have de-configured for Failover for the VLAN 354 Scope and removed Amsterdam DHCP server from DHCP helper
- Only kept local DHCP server as helper for VLAN 354 however still same issue observed. Means local DHCP server was also not working.
- Asked AD Team to perform failover and make Local DHCP Server as a primary & Remote DHCP server as Secondary
- Involved Zscaler to check issue and observed DHCP Request sent to Amsterdam DHCP server however no response.
- Local IT confirmed that other VLANs machine also slowly getting affected as lease getting Expiring.
- Decided to move Affected DHCP scope to Local Site Core switch.
- Observed Error while configuring DHCP Scopes on local Site Core switch so involved Cisco TAC for help
- Cisco TAC didn't find anything so suggested to Failover services on standby module (5 mins downtime) which was not agreed considering 24/7 Operational site.
- Cisco TAC suggested to perform software upgrade and reboot Core switch (1 hr maintenance window) which was also not agreed considering 24/7 Operational site.
- During Cisco Call, FAN Liu suggested option to configure DHCP Scope on Distribution/Access Switch.
- Aside Local IT helped to install Wireshark on one of the Affected machine and observed DHCP request sent however no reply.
- AD Team also installed Wireshark on DHCP server however we were not able to apply filter to capture DHCP traffic.
- Meantime we successfully shifted DHCP Scope for vlan 354 on Distribution switch and local IT confirmed its working.
- We decided to move all affected DHCP scopes to Distribution Switch as more machines reporting issue as lease was getting expire.
- We moved below DHCP Scopes to Distribution switch and local IT confirmed all are working fine.

AZUREUW-DB018 RDP not working post change activity - 10610 - Warwick - United Kingdom - 27th Aug 2025
u_root_cause:
Below point can be a root cause of RDS break after domain migration 
1. Broken Trust Relationship RDS servers may no longer trust the new domain or have lost trust with the domain controller
2.Licensing Configuration RDS licensing server might still be pointing to the old domain or using domain-based licensing. 
3. User Profile Service Failures Users may not be able to log in due to profile path issues or SID mismatches. 
4. NLA (Network Level Authentication) Issues If NLA is enabled, and the domain trust is broken, RDP connections may fail.

short_description: P2 - Internet Connectivity dropping out due to Network Flap
u_root_cause:
Summary of the Case:
Multiple disruptions across sites, especially Warwick: 
•	SAP and Wi-Fi instability.
•	DMVPN tunnel flaps.
•	LAN/Wi-Fi issues.
•	Access Point flaps.
RCA – 
ISP1 dropouts did not trigger proper failover to ISP2, affecting Zscaler connectivity and LAN performance. 
Interfering scripts impacted NAT behaviour and session handling, causing false tunnel down events.

short_description: P2 - Switch down 282-UK-SWA24-L2
RCA_INC7635801 - Network Connectivity Issues: PHINIA SSID Unavailable & Performance Lag - 00269 - Izmir - Turkey
u_root_cause:
Key Observations:
•	No configuration changes were made during troubleshooting; connectivity restored on its own initially.
•	Recent migration of Izmir and SLP sites from Miami vCenter to Amsterdam vCenter (MS15), including WLC and VMs (Change ID: CHG0530105).
•	Authentication errors identified; stale Zscaler entries removed.
•	ISP involvement suspected of external validation issues.
Root Cause:
Intermittent wireless connectivity failures due to stale Zscaler entries and transient authentication issues, compounded by recent infrastructure migration.
